# Workflow: Git Commit
# Purpose: Guide Conventional Commits
# Usage: workflow check examples/git/commit.workflow.list

- (start) Git Commit
  - import: commit-validate.workflow.list
  - import: commit-message.workflow.list

- (confirm) Confirm
  - Ask: Commit? (yes/no)
  - @confirm[1]: Confirmed?

- Execute: git commit -m "<message>"
- End
